## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of comprehensive, large-scale studies directly comparing organic and conventional farming across all environmental metrics. Additionally, the environmental impact of farming practices can vary significantly based on local conditions, crop types, and specific farming methods, which may not be fully captured in the studies referenced. Furthermore, the debate is often polarized, with strong opinions on both sides, which can influence the interpretation of data.